<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 3:27PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Putnam
and southern Jasper Counties through 400 PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near McElheneys Crossroads,
or 7 miles south of Monticello, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Monticello, McElheneys Crossroads, Stanfordville, Adgateville, and
Hillsboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
